gallery.title: Oregon Ducks softball wins 7-5 handing No. 3 UCLA Bruins first loss of the season

image.caption: Oregon pitcher Miranda Elish and the Ducks handed unbeaten UCLA their first out of the season at the Ducks hold on to beat the Bruins 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon pitcher, Miranda Elish (left facing), celebrates with her team after closing out the top of the second inning as the Ducks hold on to beat UCLA 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's DJ Sanders turns a double play over the Bruins Jenna Crawford in the fourth inning as Oregon holds on to beat UCLA 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
Oregon's Shannon Rhodes makes on out in the third inning en route to beat UCLA 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Jenna Lilley (left), Miranda Elish, and Mia Camuso celebrate a double play in the fourth inning as the Ducks hold on to beat UCLA 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
Oregon pitcher, Miranda Elish, watches a strike en route to the Ducks 7-5 win over UCLA in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's DJ Sanders (left), avoids the effort by the Bruins, Kylee Perez, after Sanders double in the fifth inning as the Ducks hold on to beat UCLA 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Jenna Lilley celebrates the Ducks final out of the fifth inning as Ducks hold on to beat UCLA 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

The Bruins, Holly Azevedo, can't contain a base-loading hit by Oregon's, Haley Cruse, in the fourth inning as the Ducks hold on to beat UCLA 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

ULCA gather at home plate after a three-run home run by Aaliyah Jordan in the third inning as the Ducks hold on to beat UCLA 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Mia Camuso (center) reacts to the Ducks ending of their fifth inning en route to Oregon's 7-5 win over UCLA at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Mary Iakopo connects for a double RBI in the fifth inning as the Ducks hold on to beat UCLA 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Mary Iakopo (right) hi-fives Haley Cruse after Iakopo scored on a Bruins wild pitch in the fourth inning as Oregon holds on to beat UCLA 7-5 at Jane Saunders Stadium in Eugene on Saturday, March 17, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
